<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870310-0095 </DOCNO><HL> Control Data to BoostMagnetic PeripheralsStock Holding to 80%</HL><DD> 03/10/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CDA UIS HONTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> MINNEAPOLIS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Control Data Corp. said it signed a letter of intent to increase its ownership to 80% in Magnetic Peripherals Inc., a joint venture managed by its Data Storage Products Group.    Under the agreement, Control Data, a computer concern, said it agreed to buy Unisys Inc.'s 13% interest in the joint venture. Terms weren't disclosed.    Magnetic Peripherals was founded in 1975 to maintain a technological base in data storage and supply peripheral equipment for the computer systems of its owners. Now it primarily makes high-capacity data storage products sold by Control Data to computer systems manufacturers world-wide, the company said.    Honeywell Inc.'s Information Systems division owns 14% of Magnetic Peripherals and Bull S.A. of France owns 6%.    The company said that under the agreement Unisys will become a customer of its Data Storage Products Group over a two-year period and Control Data will continue to furnish disk drives to Unisys.    Unisys, a business machines, data processing and aerospace products concern, is based in Detroit and Honeywell, a diversified computer concern, in Minneapolis. </TEXT></DOC>